<p>Here's your new toolbox from this tutorial:</p>

<table class="cheat-Sheet">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Code</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<strong>' %></code> / <code><%= '<em>' %></code></td><td>Bold importance / italic emphasis</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<br>' %></code></td><td>A line break, exactly where you put it (no closing tag)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<hr>' %></code></td><td>A divider line across the page (no closing tag)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<blockquote>' %></code></td><td>A quotation, set apart from your text</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>&amp;hearts;</code> etc.</td><td>Entities: special symbols like &hearts; and &starf;</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<!-- ... -->' %></code></td><td>A comment: invisible notes and secret messages</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<details>' %></code> + <code><%= '<summary>' %></code></td><td>A click-to-reveal box</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>id="name"</code> + <code><%= '<a href="#name">' %></code></td><td>Jump links to spots on the same page</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<div class="name">' %></code></td><td>An invisible, nameable box for grouping things</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>The editor shows the page you built across this tutorial. It stays saved in your browser, so you can come back and tinker &mdash; or copy your favorite tricks to your real site from the <a href="/dashboard">dashboard</a>.</p>

